commit.message:
Update jose to 1.11.5, but use 1.11.1 on Erlang/OTP older than 21

Erlang older than 21 does not support
  try catch _Class:_Reason:_Stacktrace ->
that is used in jose_server.erl
Put kernel and stdlib first, they are started in that order
Update Jiffy to 1.1.1 to support compiling with Mix again
Test with Erlang/OTP 25, but old rebar2 is not supported
Update Jiffy to 1.1.0, to support Erlang/OTP 25.0-rc1
Copy code from eimp to use override_deps_versions only when not rebar3
Change README syntax to make it recognizable by doc converter
Install libyaml-dev before issuing hex publish
Actions: test default compilation, that is with rebar2
Generate documentation for hex.pm from README.md and EDoc
Sometimes rebar3.crashdump is not generated, use DEBUG option instead
Fix support for jose 1.11.1 in: rebar2 compilation, rebar3 xref
Update Jose to 1.11.1 (the last in hex.pm correctly versioned)
